-- Tanzanian Exports Doubled Over Four Years on Minerals, Daily News Reports
-- Sarah McGregor
-- 2010-07-02T05:56:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/tanzanian-exports-doubled-over-four-years-on-minerals-daily-news-reports.html

          
          
             Tanzania ’s exports earnings almost
doubled between 2005 and 2009 with mineral shipments accounting
for about half of the value of sales abroad, the  Daily News 
reported, citing Trade Minister  Mary Nagu .  
 Shipments increased to $3.1 billion last year compared with
$1.7 billion in 2005, the state-run Dar es Salaam-based
newspaper reported today.  
 The main buyers of Tanzania’s goods last year included
Japan, China, Hong Kong, India, the United Arab Emirates,
European Union nations, and countries in east and southern
Africa, the newspaper said.  
